        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Firefox Version 33'); ?>
        <p><strong>Firefox 33</strong> was released on 14 October 2014. It now has off-main-thread compositing (OMTC) enabled by default on <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows', 'OS'); ?> (which brings responsiveness improvements), OpenH264 support, search suggestions on <code>about:home</code> and <code>about:newtab</code>, address bar search improvements, session restore reliability improvements, and other changes.</p>
        <p>Firefox 33.0.1 was released for desktop only on 24 October 2014, fixing displaying of a black screen at startup with certain graphics drivers. Firefox 33.0.2 was released for desktop only on 28 October 2014, fixing a startup crash with some combination of hardware and drivers. Firefox 33.0.3 was released for desktop only on 6 November 2014, fixing several issues related to graphics drivers.</p>
        <p>Firefox 33.1 was released on 10 November 2014, celebrating Firefox's 10 year anniversary. Firefox 33.1.1 was released for desktop only on 14 November 2014, fixing a startup crash.</p>
